==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Maculate
<hw>Mac"u*late</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>maculatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>maculare</ets> to spot. See
<er>Macula</er>, and cf. <er>Macule</er>, <pos>v.</pos>]</ety> <def>To
spot; to stain; to blur.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Maculate</qex> the honor of their people.</q> <rj><qau>Sir T.
Elyot.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Maculate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Maculate
<hw>Mac"u*late</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>maculatus</ets>, p. p.]</ety> <def>Marked with spots or maculae;
blotched; hence, defiled; impure; <as>as, most <ex>maculate</ex>
thoughts</as>.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Maculated</ent>⟦br⟧
